         <abstract id="aspace_7ff12e9d4ae3974bcf1574febd876622">This collection contains early American bookplates designed and engraved by Nathaniel Hurd (1730-1777), a silversmith and engraver born in Boston. His armorial bookplate designs are in the Jacobean and Chippendale styles, following the English fashion.</abstract>
    
